section.section:
"Credit agreement" means a covenant, promise, undertaking, commitment, or other agreement by a financial institution to:
Lend money;
Forbear from repayment of money, goods, or things in action;
Forbear from collecting or exercising any right to collect a debt; or
Otherwise extend credit.

"Financial institution" means:
A bank;
A trust company;
A savings bank;
A savings and loan association; or
An affiliate or subsidiary of a bank, trust company, savings bank, or savings and loan association.

text.section:
A credit agreement is not enforceable by way of action or defense unless it:
Is in writing;
Expresses consideration;
Sets forth the relevant terms and conditions of the agreement; and
Is signed by the person against whom its enforcement is sought.
